ll)#Striker|Striker]]\n| currentclub         = [[TSV 1860 Munich|1860 Munich]]\n| clubnumber          = 24\n| youthyears1         = 1998\u20132005\n| youthclubs1         = SpVgg Neukirchen-Balbini\n| youthyears2         = 2005\u20132007\n| youthclubs2         = [[SSV Jahn Regensburg|Jahn Regensburg]]\n| youthyears3         = 2007\u20132010\n| youthclubs3         = [[TSV 1860 Munich|1860 Munich]]\n| years1              = 2010\u20132013\n| clubs1              = [[TSV 1860 Munich II|1860 Munich II]]\n| caps1               = 70\n| goals1              = 26\n| years2              = 2011\u20132013\n| clubs2              = [[TSV 1860 Munich|1860 Munich]]\n| caps2               = 4\n| goals2              = 0\n| years3              = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs3              = [[FSV Frankfurt]]\n| caps3               = 5\n| goals3              = 1\n| years4              = 2014\n| clubs4              = \u2192 [[SV Darmstadt 98|Darmstadt 98]] (loan)\n| caps4               = 6\n| goals4              = 0\n| years5              = 2014\n| clubs5              = [[Chemnitzer FC]]\n| caps5               = 21\n| goals5              = 0\n| years6              = 2015\u20132017\n| clubs6              = [[SSV Jahn Regensburg|Jahn Regensburg]]\n| caps6               = 41\n| goals6              = 19\n| years7              = 2017\u2013\n| clubs7              = [[TSV 1860 Munich|1860 Munich]]\n| caps7               = 50\n| goals7              = 15\n| nationalyears1      = 2007\u20132008\n| nationalteam1       = [[Germany national youth football team#Germany national under-16 squad|Germany U16]]\n| nationalcaps1       = 5\n| nationalgoals1      = 0\n| medaltemplates      = \n| club-update         = 15:27, 16 January 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n'''Markus Ziereis''' (born 26 August 1992) is a German [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[TSV 1860 Munich]].<ref name=\"kicker\">{{cite web | url = http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/regionalliga/rlby/regionalliga-bayern-2012/2017-18/1860-muenchen-5/43618/spieler_markus-ziereis.html | title = Markus Ziereis | language = de | website = kicker.de | access-date = 10 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\nZiereis began his career with [[TSV 1860 Munich]] and made his [[2. Bundesliga]] debut for the club in November 2012, as a half-time substitute for [[Sebastian Maier]] in a 2\u20132 draw with [[1. FC Union Berlin]]. In 2013, he joined [[FSV Frankfurt]].<ref name=\"Jahn\">{{cite web | url = http://www.ssv-jahn.de/profis/news/2983 | title = Jahn holt Ziereis zur\u00fcck nach Hause | website = SSV Jahn Regensburg | date = 17 June 2015 | access-date = 25 July 2015}}</ref> In order to get more playing time, he was loaned to [[SV Darmstadt 98]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.fsv-frankfurt.de/cms/index.php?id=15&tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=6958&cHash=6543211419de27ec4aa831b368f3f4df | title = FSV verleiht Markus Ziereis an Darmstadt 98 | language = German | publisher = FSV Frankfurt | date = 3 January 2014 | accessdate = 3 January 2014}}</ref> In 2014, he joined [[Chemnitzer FC]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.focus.de/regional/frankfurt-am-main/fussball-fussballer-ziereis-verlaesst-fsv-frankfurt-richtung-chemnitz_id_3952213.html | title = St\u00fcrmer Markus Ziereis wechselt vom Fu\u00dfball-Zweitligisten FSV Frankfurt zum Drittligisten Chemnitzer FC. | language = de | website = Focus Online | date = 27 June 2014 | access-date = 25 July 2015}}</ref>\n\nAfter one season, he returned to [[SSV Jahn Regensburg]].<ref name=\"Jahn\" /> During the 2015\u201316 season he contributed 19 goals in 31 league matches to Regensburg's promotion from the [[Regionalliga Bayern]] to the [[3. Liga]].<ref name=\"1860munich\">{{cite news|title=Regensburgs Ziereis unterschreibt bei 1860|url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/regionalliga/startseite/703624/artikel_regensburgs-ziereis-unterschreibt-bei-1860.html|accessdate=10 August 2017|work=kicker Online|date=10 August 2017|language=German}}</ref> His following season was blighted by injuries and he lost his place in the starting lineup, making just 10 substitute appearances.<ref name=\"1860munich\"/>\n\nOn 10 August 2017, Ziereis returned to 1860 Munich, thereby moving two tiers down, leaving newly promoted [[2. Bundesliga]] club Regensburg to play in the Regionalliga Bayern.<ref name=\"1860munich\"/>\n\n==International career==\nIn 2007 and 2008, Ziereis earned five caps for the Germany under-16 national team.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://datencenter.dfb.de/profil/224289 | title = Markus Ziereis | language = German | publisher = datencenter.dfb.de | accessdate = 10 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nZiereis is best friends with [[Kevin Volland]]. The duo shared a flat while playing together at [[TSV 1860 Munich]] as they both played for [[Bavarian Football Association]] youth teams.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Scharf|first1=J\u00fcrgen|title=Ziereis sorgt f\u00fcr Tore \u2013 und Stimmung|url=http://www.mittelbayerische.de/sport/regional/regensburg-nachrichten/ziereis-sorgt-fuer-tore-und-stimmung-21524-art1376754.html|accessdate=29 May 2016|work=[[Mittelbayerische Zeitung]]|date=10 May 2016|language=German}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Doppelpack: Wird Ziereis ein Kandidat f\u00fcr Maurer?|url=http://www.merkur.de/sport/amateur-fussball/landkreis-muenchen-stadt/doppelpack-wird-ziereis-kandidat-maurer-2527728.html|accessdate=29 May 2016|work=[[M\u00fcnchner Merkur]]|date=30 September 2012|language=German}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Leischwitz|first1=Christoph|title=In der Reifephase|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/muenchen/sport/tsv-muenchen-talente-in-der-reifephase-1.1017400|accessdate=29 May 2016|work=S\u00fcddeutsche Zeitung|date=28 October 2010|language=German}}</ref> Volland was also witness when Ziereis married Evi Reiter on 28 December 2018.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.mittelbayerische.de/region/regensburg-stadt-nachrichten/mz-moderatorin-evi-reiter-sagte-ja-21179-art1733986.html | title = MZ-Moderatorin Evi Reiter sagte Ja | trans-title = MZ moderator Evi Reiter said yes | language = de | website = Mittelbayerische Zeitung | date = 28 December 2018 | access-date = 28 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{Updated|match played 21 December 2019}}<ref>{{Soccerway|markus-ziereis/141841|access-date=16 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[DFB-Pokal]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[TSV 1860 Munich II|1860 Munich II]]\n|[[2010\u201311 Regionalliga#Regionalliga S\u00fcd|2010\u201311]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Regionalliga S\u00fcd (1994\u20132012)|Regionalliga S\u00fcd]]\n|10||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||10||0\n|-\n|[[2011\u201312 Regionalliga#Regionalliga S\u00fcd|2011\u201312]]\n|27||4||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||27||4\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 Regionalliga#Regionalliga Bayern|2012\u201313]]\n|[[Regionalliga Bayern]]\n|35||22||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||35||22\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!72!!26!!0!!0!!72!!26\n|-\n|[[TSV 1860 Munich|1860 Munich]]\n|[[2012\u201313 2. Bundesliga|2012\u201313]]\n|[[2. Bundesliga]]\n|4||0||0||0||4||0\n|-\n|[[FSV Frankfurt]]\n|[[2013\u201314 2. Bundesliga|2013\u201314]]\n|[[2. Bundesliga]]\n|5||1||0||0||5||1\n|-\n|[[SV Darmstadt 98|Darmstadt 98]] (loan)\n|[[2013\u201314 3. Liga|2013\u201314]]\n|[[3. Liga]]\n|6||0||0||0||6||0\n|-\n|[[Chemnitzer FC|Chemnitzer]]\n|[[2014\u201315 3. Liga|2014\u201315]]\n|[[3. Liga]]\n|21||0||1||1||22||1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[SSV Jahn Regensburg|Jahn Regensburg]]\n|[[2015\u201316 Regionalliga#Regionalliga Bayern|2015\u201316]]\n|[[Regionalliga Bayern]]\n|33||19||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||33||19\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 3. Liga|2016\u201317]]\n|[[3. Liga]]\n|10||0||0||0||10||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!43!!19!!0!!0!!43!!19\n|-\n|ro